<subSubSection id="C34D656DFF97FFECFF57FE3DFBABFDA4" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE836E6FF97FFECFF57FE3DFD82FE30" blockId="48.[151,1436,426,783]" box="[151,587,426,451]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B923EAF4FF97FFECFF57FE3DFE49FE30" bold="true" box="[151,384,426,451]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Material examined.</emphasis>
A23325; A 6431.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E6FF97FFECFF07FE45FBABFDA4" blockId="48.[151,1436,426,783]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B923EAF4FF97FFECFF07FE45FEB9FE18" bold="true" box="[199,368,466,491]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Identification.</emphasis>
Test fragile, small, aborally raised. Apical disc with single genial plate (monobasal) in males, four gonopores; in females evolved to a brooding structure. Peristome sub-central, no bourrelets. Ambulacra simple, non-petaloid arrangement, pores small orally, none aboral. Primary tubercles slightly perforated, crenulated. Spines short, uniform, densely covering marsupium. Test and spines white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D656DFF97FFECFF07FDF2FD31FD35" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE836E6FF97FFECFF07FDF2FCDEFD8D" blockId="48.[151,1436,426,783]" box="[199,791,613,638]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B923EAF4FF97FFECFF07FDF2FE1BFD8D" bold="true" box="[199,466,613,638]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Global maximum size.</emphasis>
Maximum test length 
<quantity id="4CAF9B03FF97FFECFD0FFDF1FCDAFD8D" box="[719,787,614,638]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
